   <text>
      <body>
         
            
               <p>Erasmus Aulonita (Gerasimos Avlonites) traveled <placeName>Europe</placeName> and
                     <placeName>England</placeName> from <date when="1752">1752</date> through at
                  least <date when="1773">1773</date>, claiming to be a displaced (Greek) Orthodox
                  Bishop of <placeName>Arcadia in Crete</placeName>. <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> turned to Erasmus for the
                  ordination of his (educationally qualified) lay preacher <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers1179.xml"/>John Jones</persName> in the summer of <date when="1763">1763</date>. Some other Methodist lay preachers (without the
                  educational qualifications) then paid Erasmus to ordain them in late <date when="1765">1765</date>, and received <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>'s censure for this
                  action. See A. B. Sackett, 'John Wesley and the Greek Orthodox Bishop',
                     <hi rend="italic">WHS</hi> 38 (<date from="1971" to="1972">1971–72</date>):
                  81–88, 97–102.</p>
            
         
